<subSubSection box="[577,1011,1617,1644]" pageId="21" pageNumber="115" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="21.[577,1011,1617,1644]" box="[577,1011,1617,1644]" pageId="21" pageNumber="115">
Subfamily 
<taxonomicName authority="Fan, 1965" authorityName="Fan" authorityYear="1965" box="[707,1011,1617,1644]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Atherigoninae">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[707,886,1617,1643]" pageId="21" pageNumber="115">Atherigoninae</emphasis>
Fan, 1965
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="115" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,1399,1683,1744]" pageId="21" pageNumber="115">
This subfamily includes only one large genus of morphologically deviant 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[1091,1209,1683,1709]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Muscidae</taxonomicName>
. It is obviously monophyletic, but its relationships remain uncertain.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,690,1791,1818]" box="[189,690,1791,1818]" pageId="21" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis box="[189,199,1792,1817]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="115">•</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Rondani, 1856" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1856" box="[213,525,1791,1818]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Atherigona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[213,345,1791,1817]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="115">Atherigona</emphasis>
Rondani, 1856
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[541,681,1791,1817]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,232,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,704,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-127@22.[189,1399,704,1911]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 11. Atherigona orientalis Schiner, 1868, ♀. A. Wing, ventral view. B. Detail of wing showing CS1‒3, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6784153" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6784153/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="115">Fig. 11A–B</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,1398,1837,1969]" pageId="21" pageNumber="115">
A total of 20+ named and unidentified species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1856" box="[842,974,1837,1863]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Atherigona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[842,974,1837,1863]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="115">Atherigona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Old World tropics and Mediterranean subregion were examined. They invariably share state 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1029,1065,1872,1898]" pageId="21" pageNumber="115">A0</emphasis>
, in which vein C is wholly bare ventrally behind the lower anterior row of alternating spinules and setulae, as exemplified by 
<taxonomicName authority="Schiner, 1868" authorityName="Schiner" authorityYear="1868" box="[189,503,1943,1969]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Atherigona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis box="[189,334,1943,1969]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="115">A. orientalis</emphasis>
Schiner, 1868
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[519,662,1943,1969]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,232,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,704,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-127@22.[189,1399,704,1911]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 11. Atherigona orientalis Schiner, 1868, ♀. A. Wing, ventral view. B. Detail of wing showing CS1‒3, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6784153" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6784153/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="115">Fig. 11A–B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
